OL,5, A former secretary who worked for the  
OL,6, commander of a Nazi concentration camp 
OL,7, has been convicted of complicity in the
OL,8, murders of more than 10,500 people.    
OL,10,FIrmgard Furchner, 97, was taken on as a
OL,11,Fteenaged shorthand typist at Stutthof  
OL,12,Fand worked there from 1943 to 1945.    
OL,14,FFurchner, the first woman to be tried  
OL,15,Ffor Nazi crimes in decades, was given a
OL,16,Ftwo-year suspended jail term.          
OL,18,FAlthough she was a civilian worker, the
OL,19,Fjudge agreed she was fully aware of    
OL,20,Fwhat was going on at the camp.         
